      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Family Members Papers</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The bulk of the collection consists of correspondence and other papers of individual family members, much of which details their activities in the Philippine Islands from 1907 to 1912. Winifred Hubbell, in particular, wrote detailed accounts of the family's journey to the Philippines and of their experiences there in letters to her mother, Martha Waters. In 1912 Winifred traveled to Germany with the children and wrote frequently to Clarence who remained in the Philippines. The following year the family returned to Michigan but Clarence had to return to the Philippines to finish his work. His letters to Winifred during this period reflect the changing attitudes of Filipinos towards Americans.</p>
          <p>Among the personal papers of Winifred and Clarence Hubbell, the researcher will find autobiographical material concerning, in part, their experiences while growing up in Benzonia, Michigan. The papers of Theodore Hubbell reflect his involvement in the bicentennial project on historic houses in Benzonia and a reunion of Benzonia Academy graduates.</p>
        </scopecontent>
